Initializing git on local ubuntu server and adding it to epam github repo:

mkdir jenkins
git init
git checkout -b jenkins
touch README
git add README
git commit -m "readme" README
git remote add origin https://github.com/princeblr/epam
git push origin jenkins

Adding build.xml to local repo and pushing it to github repo:

git add build.xml
git commit -m "jenkins build.xml for app" build.xml
git push origin jenkins

install ant 
sudo apt-get install ant
set JAVA_HOME or use ansible java role to set the same auto


Jenkins installation on Vagrant Ubuntu VM machine:
Following: https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Installing+Jenkins+on+Ubuntu
downloaded jenkins war from https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/
Make sure ports are forwarded in vagrantfile

Plugins installation :
Checkstyle Plug-in
Static Analysis Collector Plug-in
Using checkstyle-7.4 

Build location : /opt/jenkins/sudoku
Java Source location : /opt/jenkins
Source location files : build.xml  checkstyle-7.4  checkstyle-7.4-all.jar  src
Changing folder permission for jenkins user : 
sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /opt/jenkins

Configuring jenkins job using config.xml uploaded for easy configuration.

To build the project locally:
#ant 
#ant checkstyle
This should build dist, build directories in the same location and checkstyle reports are contained in build directory.




